점원by점원인데 한국인이면 가지마셈.. 불친절한 직원 만날 가능성 있음 ㅠㅠ 괜히 기분만 잡쳤네 Could anyone please tell the workers, a man and a woman, who worked at around 12:50pm July 7 that their service was horrible? I ordered two Iced Guava White Lemonade, and they made one correctly, and the other wrong. It was not a guava, so I asked them that this is not the thing I ordered. The guy made mine again, but it was the same wrong thing (guess it was a peach lemonade or sth). So the woman made it again. I guess the man was new worker or sth. They NEVER said sorry though they wasted my time. Time is a very important thing to tourists, and I am a tourist. The woman especially seemed very annoyed. Thanks for ruining and wasting my time at Starbucks!

The young girl taking my order was super kind and I didn’t catch her name. But my drink was made wrong, no big deal but I go to tell the staff that it was supposed to be iced and have extra matcha and I get zero eye contact she takes the hot drink doesn’t listen to the a word I say and dumps the hot one down the sink. She makes an iced one but still not how I asked. She was angry and I am not about to make her more mad. But then that’s so annoying I pay for my drink and pay for the extra matcha, I understand people have bad days but I didn’t do anything but try to get a drink I paid for. And if this was just happening this once I wouldn’t care I would shrug it off but This keeps happening at Starbucks around New York. So basically I am tired of paying for stuff at Starbucks not getting it made how I asked and getting attitude when trying to fix it. I don’t want to have bad vibes I just want my caffeine.

RUDE! It's such a toss up to come to this starbucks instead of the express one or the one down by the river- which always have top notch service. I feel like everytime I go it's super backed up and they DO NOT listen to your order- they just make it however and hope you don't notice. I ordered a sandwich and was standing in the busy store today when it was flown at me and the employee announced "Here it is you walked right past it" Also, you can watch them make your drink wrong and then they get pissy about it. I wish these employees had some customer service training. On the other hand every once in a while if it is slow I get two employees that are always so nice and will even look for something in the back for you if you can't find it- these employees were two of the only male employees I have seen there.
